<br>
Yes this is a good point.  A Skalds defense is balanced against its parrying ability but cant be speced high while the other classes included in this list have other factors contributing to their defensive abilitys.<br>
<br>
The only other classes that fall into this category are :<br>
<br>
Friar - Leather + Evade 5 + high AF buff + parry<br>
Valewalker -  Evade 4 + AF buff + absorb buff (basicly plate -2% abs thats neutral to everything) + parry<br>
Warden - Scale + 6 sec pulseing bladeturn (read 100% melee absorb every 6 seconds) + parry<br>
Savage - Studded + Evade 4 + advanced evade + self shout buffs + parry<br>
Minstrel (although not a parry class) - Chain armour + evade 2 + high dex/qui + absorb chant<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
We should clearly have either higher evade or some type of self buff or a group effect defensive chant.  Some of these classes even have the option not to a melee and just fill a support role while a Skald must always melee.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
