<br>
Lets say you click on damage add, and run speed in that order, and keep those going.  Then you run into some nuker group, and you click on a resist chant.  This would turn &quot;off&quot; the &quot;first&quot; song you turned on - in this case the damage add, and turn &quot;on&quot; the resist song - leaving the run song and the resist song on.<br>
<br>
I don't think it would be impossible to do, but I acknowledge that given my perception of Mythic's opinion of skalds (which seems to not at all be consistent with most of the people actually playing skalds) that they're unlikely to do any major change.<br>
<br>
If the question was related to the role-playing aspects of singing 2 songs at the same time I'm not really sure how to respond since so many other classes have so many abilities that can be done at the same time - including skalds. (ie we can sing a song, and do all sorts of shouts while we're singing)<br>
<br>
Personally - I'd like to see them implement something along these lines at the very least:<br>
<br>
reduce timer on shouts to 15 sec<br>
stun shout (as minstrel)<br>
group song radius increased<br>
evade 2 and access to dodger RA<br>
<br>
And of course, they need to fix our RA... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=whorde>whorde</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Fervent</span><br>  Posts: 127<br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/9/03 11:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=655.topic&index=27>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Feedback from our 1.62 Skald Report</span><hr size=1> too many novels in this thread.  not every line needs to be responded to.  there were three things i noted as being most important.  they are, in order:<br>
